    "summary": "Illustrates the process a farmer follows to create and register a product on a blockchain, including ID generation, MetaMask confirmation, and QR code gene",
    "whatItShows": "This flowchart details the steps involved in a farmer creating and registering a product on a blockchain. It begins with the farmer initiating product creation, leading to the generation of a unique product ID. This ID is then submitted to the blockchain, requiring confirmation via MetaMask. Once the transaction is mined, a QR code is generated for the product and stored in Firebase.",
    "whenToUse": "Use this diagram to explain the initial phase of a blockchain-based supply chain system, specifically focusing on product origination and registration by a producer. It's suitable for demonstrating how physical products are linked to digital identities on a distributed ledger.",
    "howToAdapt": "This diagram can be adapted to include specific smart contract interactions, different blockchain platforms (e.g., Ethereum, Polygon), or alternative storage solutions instead of Firebase. Additional steps for quality checks, batching, or integration with IoT devices could also be incorporated.",
